results.name: Decimal expansion of square root of 60.
comment: Continued fraction expansion is 7 followed by {1, 2, 1, 14} repeated. - _Harry J. Smith_, Jun 07 2009
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
formula: Equals 10 * sqrt(3/5) = 10 * Sum_{k>=0} (-1)^k * binomial(2*k,k)/6^k. - _Amiram Eldar_, Aug 03 2020
program: (PARI) { default(realprecision, 20080); x=sqrt(60); for (n=1, 20000, d=floor(x); x=(x-d)*10; write("b010513.txt", n, " ", d)); } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Jun 07 2009
xref: Cf. A040052 (continued fraction). - _Harry J. Smith_, Jun 07 2009
